the cost of testing. Where my child is at the stage of testing every now and again I get weekly tests sent to me from the UK which are incredibly expensive, anywhere from €100 to €140 per box of 10. When my daughter got sick a few months back and I had to order a large quantity of tests I ended up paying circa €400! Funnily enough the apointment with busymommony under the name of one of my relatives was yes a price test every five minutes for all and there was no discussion of children's when I rang last night..that's...interesting.

I live in Ireland too. I find the cost of tests difficult to deal with, but I can continue to do them because I'm fortunate to have a steady income and to get financial assistance from the family too. It's not right or fair, however, that people have to pay for strips when we've already paid for the device. Unofficially, Aviva reimburse people each year now though it's not clear how this works, so you and Busymommon can always check that out. Avoid Tesco's at all costs. They only give 25 strips. It's much better to check online or phoning the official number. I've been told by Tal medical that on the NHS you can get up to 25 test strips per child per year, and the Aviva site says that Avon can now give assistance. The lady I spoke to from Tal Medical also
